2:18 Defendant Rebecca Lynn Holm in court, in custody.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 15CF103 heard at this time. OSullivan: DPA on 15CF103 #1; modify to include treatment in lieu of comply with conditions of probation. Requests time served with 36 days credit. Agent Minder addresses treatment.  Def agrees. Court: grants requests and amended DPA to reflect getting treatment in lieu of complying with conditions of probation. Court: sentences Def to time served on 15CF77 and 15CF103. Atty OSullivan to draft an order and Court will sign.
filed by Probation and Parole Agent Charysse Minder

10:52  Defendant Rebecca Lynn Holm in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 15CF103 heard at this time. Rory: dismiss Ct#1,2 in 15CT77 and Ct#2 in 15CF103. Guilty to Ct#3 in 15CF77 and Ct#1 and #3 in 15CF103. DPA on Ct#1 in 15CF103. 2 year  probation on Ct#3 in each count. Nelson and Def agree.   Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to Ct#1 and Ct#3 in 15CF103 and  Ct#3 in 15CF77; Nelson stipulates to a factual basis.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of CT#1 and #3 in 15CF103. Dismisses Ct#2. finds and adjudicates Def guilty Ct#3 in 15CF77. Dismises Ct#1 and Ct#2. OSullivan and Nelson address sentencing. Nelson requests expungement. OSullivan: willing to file amended information on 15CF77. willing to file an amended information on 15CF103 with charging just 2 counts. Court addresses expungement with a dismissed count on 15CF103. Willing to expunge the charge but not the detail. Court will grants expungement upon successful completion of probation on Ct#3 on both cases. Court questions Def. Court:   Court withholds judgment of conviction on Ct#1 in 15CF103. Accepts and approves DPA; Signs. Court: S/W 2 years probation on Ct#3 in each case, concurrent. Conditions: expungement upon successful completion of probation. court costs. DNA sample and surcharge. any conditions imposed by Agent. Appeal rights given. Dismissals will be taken care of with amended information.

Information Filed with the Court and a copy is given to the defendant  Defendant has a copy of the information  and waives reading of the information.  Defendant enters not guilty plea to Ct 1, Ct 2 and Ct 3 in 15CF77 and enters not guilty plea to Ct 1, Ct 2 and Ct 3 in 15CF103 at preliminary hearing.  Not guilty plea on all counts received by the court.    Pretrial Conference to be set.  The bond will continue as ordered.

4:40 p.m.   To include 15CF103.   Defendant Rebecca Lynn Holm in court with attorney Liesl E. Nelson.  William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Written waiver of preliminary hearing is filed and the court reviews with the defendant.  Court finds defendant freely, intelligently, knowingly, and understandingly made and waives constitutional right to a preliminary hearing.  The court finds probable cause and binds defendant over for further proceedings.
